\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13172911 WN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5721260\charrsid12799702 I enjoyed it very much. Railways them days yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3810732 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5721260\charrsid12799702 Did the job alter your attitude to life generally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13172911 WN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5721260\charrsid12799702 
Yes. Yes. I thought I was doing something that - as I wanted - as I liked to do.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13172911 WN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5721260\charrsid12799702 
Then after that I - they put me in the - what they called the despatch office. That was - I went up to Edghill. And - it was - in the dispatch office they used
 to have the batches of invoices sent from all the different - depots such as Park Lane, Alexander, Sandon and Edghill itself and Canada and we used to address the envelopes. And the first envelope as I ever wrote - I - I always remember it was YNYSDDU. T
h
ey put me on the Welsh checks. So you can just fancy what I was putting up with. Llancynfeln and all that sort of thing you see. Suppose we only used to put that sample p.g. but there was Bettw-y-Coed and all them sort of names you - and - that was my job
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3810732 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5721260\charrsid12799702 That was on the Great West Section wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13172911 WN  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5721260\charrsid12799702 
Yes, but invoices used to be sent from Edghill you see - used to be sent from Liverpool area concentrated on Edghill you see, they had a dispatch office there and as I said the invoice used to be se
nt from the various depots - by the messenger boys. And we - we was in - in the dispatch office at Edghill putting them in the envelopes and then - used to take them to what we call a telegraph office and - they used to put them on the different trains fo
r the places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3810732 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5721260\charrsid12799702 Was that the job you did right up until the war?
