Well I've been on the railway all me life - fifty-one years. Oh I was every - every job on the railway bar station m
aster. That's right - every job on the railway bar station master. Junior porter, porter, parcel porter, horse and carriage porter, ticket collector, shunter, signals - signal lampman, station lamp man. Oh - horse van driver, motor parcel van driver. Guar
d. Oh yes, I was - I was a guard from 19 - let me see, 1939 to 1965.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3810732 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5721260\charrsid12799702 When you retired?
